Ex-Civil Guard Chief Jailed for Corruption
MADRID , February 26 ( Xinhua ) -- Former Civil Guard chief Luis Roldan was sentenced to 28 years in prison for corruption on Thursday .
The Madrid court also ordered Roldan to pay the government the equivalent of 11 million U.S. dollars .
Roldan was accused of embezzling public funds , fraud , bribery and five other economic crimes .
His wife was also sentenced to four years in prison on the charge of concealing her husband 's crimes .
The Roldan case has been one of the most important cases in the anti-corruption drive in Spain .
He fled his country three years ago when he was found guilty and was on the run for 10 months .
In February 1995 he was tracked down in Thailand and extradited .
